    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1303">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1303<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the Interim Committee</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1303fn1">Concerning the establishment and membership of
                        this Committee, of which <persName corresp="#p_SHL2">Stimson was Chairman,
                            see Stimson</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BHH1">Bundy</persName>,
                            <hi rend="italic">On Active Service in Peace and War</hi>, p.
                        616.</note> (<persName corresp="#p_HGL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of War</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SHL2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-16">16 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_War1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">War</hi>
                    </gloss> 32887. For <persName corresp="#p_KCWH1">Colonel Kyle</persName>’s
                        <gloss target="#t_EyesOnly1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eyes Only</hi>
                    </gloss> from <persName corresp="#p_HGL1">Harrison</persName> for Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SHL2">Stimson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Operated on this morning. Diagnosis not yet complete but results seem
                    satisfactory and already exceed expectations. Local press release necessary as
                    interest extends great distance. Dr. <persName corresp="#p_GMGLR1"
                        >Groves</persName> pleased. He returns tomorrow. I will keep you
                        posted.<note n="2" xml:id="d1303fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL2">Stimson</persName>’s diary entry for July 16
                        concludes: “… At 7:30 PM <persName corresp="#p_HGL1">Harrison</persName>’s
                        first message concerning the test of the <gloss target="#t_S11">S–1</gloss>
                        bomb arrived and I took it at once to the President’s house and showed it to
                            <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> who of course were greatly
                        interested, although the information was still in very general terms.”
                        Concerning a further discussion of the message between <persName
                            corresp="#p_SHL2">Stimson</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BJF1"
                            >Byrnes</persName>, see <ref target="#d1236fn6">document No. 1236,
                            footnote 6</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
